'''里弗斯利'''（{{lang-en|'''Riversleigh'''}}）是位於[[澳大利亞|澳大利亞]][[昆士蘭州|昆士蘭州]]西北部格雷戈里河（Gregory River）畔的著名[[化石|化石]]點。此地有從[[漸新世|漸新世]]到[[中新世|中新世]]的各種古代哺乳動物、鳥類和爬行動物化石。<ref>Archer M; Hand, Suzanne J. & Godthelp H. [1991] 2000. ''Australia's lost world: Riversleigh, World Heritage Site''. Reed, Sydney.</ref>

里弗斯利的化石都十分稀有，許多淡水中的柔軟石灰岩層都完好地保存了下來，而沒有被地質運動壓扁。<ref name="abc">{{cite news |url=http://www.abc.net.au/science/news/ancient/AncientRepublish_1567127.htm |title=Huge skulls clues to snake evolution |author=Anna Salleh |accessdate=5 August 2010 |date=16 February 2006 |work=ABC Science |publisher=[[Australian_Broadcasting_Corporation|Australian Broadcasting Corporation]] |archive-date=2012-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121111135248/http://www.abc.net.au/science/news/ancient/AncientRepublish_1567127.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref> 這意味著許多化石都是三維立體的。<ref name="dsewpc"/>

自1901年開始有在當地發現化石的記錄，<ref name="afh"/>  主要發掘活動始於1963年。1973年開始有系統地發掘。<ref name="afh"/>  1994年作為[[波特加姆拉国家公园|波特加姆拉国家公园]]的延伸部份登陸[[世界遺產|世界遺產]]。

==化石==
[[File:Lark_Quarry_Dinosaur_Trackways_footprints.jpg|thumb]]
里弗斯利的化石主要發現在石灰岩底的池塘和洞穴中，代表著從[[雨林|雨林]]到半乾旱草原的各種[[生態系統|生態系統]]。當地最古老的化石可以追溯到2500萬年前。<ref name="nch">{{cite web |url=http://www.derm.qld.gov.au/parks/boodjamulla-riversleigh/culture.html |title=Riversleigh World Heritage Site, Boodjamulla (Lawn Hill) National Park: Nature, culture and history |date=14 December 2011 |publisher=Department of Environment and Resource Management |accessdate=28 July 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20121128023247/http://www.derm.qld.gov.au/parks/boodjamulla-riversleigh/culture.html |archivedate=2012-11-28}}</ref> 化石保存程度十分完好，概括了2000萬年的哺乳動物進化史。<ref name="dsewpc">{{cite web |url=http://www.environment.gov.au/heritage/places/world/fossil-mammal-sites/index.html |title=Australian Fossil Mammal Site - Riversleigh more information |date=15 May 2008 |publisher=Department of Sustainability, Environment, Water, Population and Communities |accessdate=28 July 2012 |archive-date=2013-09-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921013805/http://www.environment.gov.au/heritage/places/world/fossil-mammal-sites/index.html |dead-url=no }}</ref> 單獨的化石點有超過200個。<ref name="afh">{{cite book |title=Australia' Fossil Heritage: A Catalogue of Important Australian Fossil Sites |last=The Australian Heritage Council |year=2012 |publisher=Csiro Publishing |isbn=0643102302 |pages=43—44 |url=http://books.google.com.au/books?id=Z_OEfLMnRVQC |accessdate=28 July 2012 |archive-date=2014-01-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140115020740/http://books.google.com.au/books?id=Z_OEfLMnRVQC |dead-url=no }}</ref>

此處共發現了三十五具[[蝙蝠|蝙蝠]]化石，是世界上蝙蝠化石最豐富的地點之一。<ref name="dsewpc"/> 這些化石點多位於山洞中。<ref name="afh"/>

此外還發現了頭骨相當完整的[[單孔目|單孔目]]動物''[[Obdurodon_dicksoni|Obdurodon dicksoni]]''，該生物為澳大利亞同類生物的研究打開了一扇窗口。此外[[袋狼|袋狼]]的化石也發現於此地。1993年發現了[[袋小齒獸|袋小齒獸]]。<ref name="bbc">{{cite news |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-10686515 |title=Cave yields marsupial fossil haul |accessdate=5 August 2010 |date=19 July 2010 |work=[[BBC_News|BBC News]] |archive-date=2015-09-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150925185256/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-10686515 |dead-url=no }}</ref> 根據此地的研究顯示，袋小齒獸可能出現於1500萬年前，大部份滅絕於1200萬年前，原因可能是氣候變化和棲息地喪失。<ref>[http://www.australiangeographic.com.au/unprecedented-journal/fossil-find-shows-marsupial-life-cycle.htm/ Fossils reveal prehistoric life cycle]{{dead link|date=十一月 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot }}. [[Australian_Geographic|Australian Geographic]]. 20 July 2010.</ref>

其他化石還顯示了澳大利亞的[[樹袋熊|樹袋熊]]如何從以雨林植物為食改為以[[桉樹|桉樹]]葉子為食。<ref name="po">{{cite news |url=http://www.physorg.com/news180469378.html |title=Loud and lazy but didn't chew gum: Ancient koalas |author=Dan Gaffney |accessdate=5 August 2010 |date=19 December 2009 |work=[[PhysOrg|PhysOrg]] |publisher=PhysOrg.com |archive-date=2019-06-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190630194847/https://phys.org/news/2009-12-loud-lazy-didnt-gum-ancient.html |dead-url=no }}</ref> 此外也發現了昆蟲和植物化石。<ref name="afh"/>

